<body>
  <h1>üìä Excel Analytics API</h1>
  <p>Welcome to the backend API for Excel Analytics. You can use the following routes to register, login, upload Excel files, view results, and download files.</p>

  <div class="route-block">
    <h2>üîê Auth Routes</h2>
    <p><strong>Register User:</strong></p>
    <code>POST https://excel-analytics-api-3u42.onrender.com/api/auth/register</code>
    <pre><code>{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "securepassword"
}</code></pre>

    <p><strong>Login User:</strong></p>
    <code>POST https://excel-analytics-api-3u42.onrender.com/api/auth/login</code>
    <pre><code>{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "securepassword"
}</code></pre>
  </div>

  <div class="route-block">
    <h2>üë§ User Routes</h2>
    <p><strong>Get All Users (Admin only):</strong></p>
    <code>GET https://excel-analytics-api-3u42.onrender.com/api/users</code>
  </div>

  <div class="route-block">
    <h2>üìÅ Excel Routes</h2>
    <p><strong>Upload Excel File:</strong></p>
    <code>POST https://excel-analytics-api-3u42.onrender.com/api/excel/upload</code>
    <p><em>Use multipart/form-data with a file input named <code>excelFile</code></em></p>

    <p><strong>Get Uploaded Files List:</strong></p>
    <code>GET https://excel-analytics-api-3u42.onrender.com/api/excel/files</code>

    <p><strong>Download Excel File:</strong></p>
    <code>GET https://excel-analytics-api-3u42.onrender.com/api/excel/download/:filename</code>
    <pre><code>Example:
GET https://excel-analytics-api-3u42.onrender.com/api/excel/download/report1.xlsx</code></pre>
  </div>

